headlines.description: — Christian Wood led a balanced attack with 21 points and eight rebounds as the Houston Rockets defeated the Detroit Pistons 116-107, handing the Pistons their 14th straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wood helps Rockets extend Pistons losing streak to 14 games

events.name: New York Knicks at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Josh Richardson scored a season-high 27 points, Jayson Tatum had 25 and the Boston Celtics beat the New York Knicks 114-107 on Saturday night with each team missing six players because of COVID-19 protocols.
headlines.shortLinkText: Richardson has season-high 27 points, Celtics beat Knicks

headlines.description: — Robin Lopez had 20 points and 10 rebounds and the Orlando Magic beat the short-handed Brooklyn Nets 100-93 on Saturday night to snap a seven-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic beat short-handed Nets to end 7-game losing streak

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet had 27 points and 12 assists, Scottie Barnes scored 21 points and the Toronto Raptors beat the short-handed Golden State Warriors 119-100 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet has 27, Raptors rout short-handed Warriors 119-100

events.name: LA Clippers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander created space to hit his winner. Then he created space for his celebration dance.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander hits 3 at buzzer, Thunder beat Clippers

headlines.description: — Cedi Osman scored 23 points, Darius Garland had 22 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers extended their winning streak to six games, beating the short-handed Milwaukee Bucks 119-90 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers beat short-handed Bucks for 6th straight victory

headlines.description: — Standing at the free-throw line, Bradley Beal told Rudy Gobert he was going to dunk on him even after the big Frenchman had blocked two of his shots in the first half.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal has season-high 37 points, Wizards beat Jazz 109-103
